205 template<typename DataType_, int k_ = 1>
206 class SineTensorStatic
207 {
208 static_assert(k_ > 0, "parameter k_ must be a positive integer");
209
210 public:
212 static DataType_ kpi()
213 {
214 return DataType_(k_) * Math::pi<DataType_>();
215 }
216
218 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x)
219 {
220 return Math::sin(kpi() * x);
221 }
222
224 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
225 {
226 return Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y);
227 }
228
230 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
231 {
232 return Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);
233 }
234
236 static DataType_ der_x(DataType_ x)
237 {
238 return kpi() * Math::cos(kpi() * x);
239 }
240
242 static DataType_ der_x(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
243 {
244 return kpi() * Math::cos(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y);
245 }
246
248 static DataType_ der_y(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)
249 {
250 return kpi() * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::cos(kpi() * y);
251 }
252
254 static DataType_ der_x(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
255 {
256 return kpi() * Math::cos(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);
257 }
258
260 static DataType_ der_y(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
261 {
262 return kpi() * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::cos(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);
263 }
264
266 static DataType_ der_z(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
267 {
268 return kpi() * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::cos(kpi() * z);
269 }
270
272 static DataType_ der_xx(DataType_ x)
273 {
274 return -Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::sin(kpi() * x);
275 }
276
278 static DataType_ der_xx(DataType_ x, DataType_ y)

293 }
294

297 {
298 return der_xy(x, y);
299 }
300
302 static DataType_ der_xx(DataType_ x, DataType_ y, DataType_ z)
303 {
304 return -Math::sqr(kpi()) * Math::sin(kpi() * x) * Math::sin(kpi() * y) * Math::sin(kpi() * z);

306

579 template<typename DataType_>
580 class ExpBubbleScalarStatic
581 {
582 public:
584 static DataType_ eval(DataType_ x)
585 {
586 return (Math::exp(-Math::sqr(DataType_(2)*x - DataType_(1))) - Math::exp(-DataType_(1))) / (DataType_(1) - Math::exp(-DataType_(1)));
587 }
588
590 static DataType_ der_x(DataType_ x)
591 {
592 return (DataType_(8)*x - DataType_(4))*Math::exp(-Math::sqr(DataType_(2)*x - DataType_(1))) / (Math::exp(-DataType_(1)) - DataType_(1));
593 }
594
596 static DataType_ der_xx(DataType_ x)
597 {
598 return (DataType_(64)*x*(DataType_(1)-x)-DataType_(8)) * Math::exp(-Math::sqr(DataType_(2)*x - DataType_(1))) / (Math::exp(-DataType_(1)) - DataType_(1));
599 }
600 }; // class ExpBubbleScalarStatic<...>

856 template<int dim_, typename DataType_>
857 class DistanceFunction :
858 public Analytic::Function
859 {
860 public:
861 static constexpr int domain_dim = dim_;
862 typedef Analytic::Image::Scalar ImageType;
863 static constexpr bool can_value = true;
864 static constexpr bool can_grad = true;
865 static constexpr bool can_hess = true;
866
867 typedef Tiny::Vector<DataType_, dim_> PointType;
868
870 template<typename EvalTraits_>
871 class Evaluator :
872 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<EvalTraits_>
873 {
874 public:
876 typedef typename EvalTraits_::DataType DataType;
878 typedef typename EvalTraits_::PointType PointType;
880 typedef typename EvalTraits_::ValueType ValueType;
882 typedef typename EvalTraits_::GradientType GradientType;
884 typedef typename EvalTraits_::HessianType HessianType;
885
886 private:
888 const PointType _origin;
889
890 public:
892 explicit Evaluator(const DistanceFunction& function) :
893 _origin(function._origin)
894 {
895 }
896
897 ValueType value(const PointType& point) const
898 {
899 return (point - _origin).norm_euclid();
900 }
901
902 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
903 {
904 DataType norm (this->value(point));
905
906 if(norm < Math::eps<DataType>())
907 return GradientType::null();
908
909 return (DataType(1) / norm) * (point - _origin);
910 }
911
912 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point) const
913 {
914 DataType norm (this->value(point));
915 if(norm < Math::eps<DataType>())
916 return HessianType::null();
917
918 HessianType hess (DataType(0));
919 norm = DataType(1)/norm;
920 DataType denom = Math::sqr(norm)*norm;
921
922 for(int i(0); i < dim_; ++i)
923 {
924 hess[i][i] = norm;
925 for(int j(0); j < dim_; ++j)
926 {
927 hess[i][j] -= ((point[i] - _origin[i]) * (point[j] - _origin[j]))*denom;
928 }
929 }
930 return hess;
931 }
932 }; // class DistanceFunction::Evaluator<...>
933
934 public:
936 PointType _origin;
937
938 public:
940 explicit DistanceFunction(const PointType& origin) :
941 _origin(origin)
942 {
943 }
944
946 void set_point(const PointType& origin)
947 {
948 _origin = origin;
949 }
950 }; // class DistanceFunction

968 template<int dim_, typename DataType_>
969 class DistanceFunctionSD :
970 public Analytic::Function
971 {
972 public:
973 static constexpr int domain_dim = dim_;
974 typedef Analytic::Image::Scalar ImageType;
975
976 static constexpr bool can_value = true;
977 static constexpr bool can_grad = true;
978 static constexpr bool can_hess = true;
979
980 typedef Tiny::Vector<DataType_, dim_> PointType;
981
983 template<typename EvalTraits_>
984 class Evaluator :
985 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<EvalTraits_>
986 {
987 public:
989 typedef typename EvalTraits_::DataType DataType;
991 typedef typename EvalTraits_::PointType PointType;
993 typedef typename EvalTraits_::ValueType ValueType;
995 typedef typename EvalTraits_::GradientType GradientType;
997 typedef typename EvalTraits_::HessianType HessianType;
998
999 private:
1001 const PointType _origin;
1003 const DataType _a, _b;
1004
1005 public:
1007 explicit Evaluator(const DistanceFunctionSD& function) :
1008 _origin(function._origin),
1009 _a(function._a),
1010 _b(function._b)
1011 {
1012 }
1013
1014 ValueType value(const PointType& point) const
1015 {
1016 return _a + _b*(point - _origin).norm_euclid();
1017 }
1018
1019 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
1020 {
1021 DataType norm ((point - _origin).norm_euclid());
1022 if(norm < Math::eps<DataType>())
1023 return GradientType::null();
1024
1025 return (_b / norm) * (point - _origin);
1026 }
1027
1028 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point) const
1029 {
1030 DataType norm ((point - _origin).norm_euclid());
1031 if(norm <= Math::eps<DataType>())
1032 return HessianType::null();
1033
1034 HessianType hess(DataType(0));
1035
1036 norm = DataType(1)/norm;
1037 DataType denom = _b*Math::sqr(norm)*norm;
1038
1039 for(int i(0); i < dim_; ++i)
1040 {
1041 hess[i][i] = _b*norm;
1042 for(int j(0); j < dim_; ++j)
1043 {
1044 hess[i][j] -= ((point[i] - _origin[i]) * (point[j] - _origin[j]))*denom;
1045 }
1046 }

1279 return HessianType::null();
1280 else if(val1 < val2)
1281 return _f1_eval.hessian(point);
1282 else
1283 return _f2_eval.hessian(point);
1284 }

1571 template<typename DataType_>
1572 class PolynomialFunction1D :
1573 public Analytic::Function
1574 {
1575 public:
1577 static constexpr int domain_dim = 1;
1579 typedef Analytic::Image::Scalar ImageType;
1581 static constexpr bool can_value = true;
1583 static constexpr bool can_grad = true;
1585 static constexpr bool can_hess = true;
1586
1588 template<typename EvalTraits_>
1589 class Evaluator :
1590 public Analytic::Function::Evaluator<EvalTraits_>
1591 {
1592 public:
1593 typedef typename EvalTraits_::DataType DataType;
1594 typedef typename EvalTraits_::PointType PointType;
1595 typedef typename EvalTraits_::ValueType ValueType;
1596 typedef typename EvalTraits_::GradientType GradientType;
1597 typedef typename EvalTraits_::HessianType HessianType;
1598
1599 private:
1601 std::vector<DataType> _coeff;
1602
1603 public:
1605 explicit Evaluator(const PolynomialFunction1D& function)
1606 {
1607 for(auto it = function._coeff.begin(); it != function._coeff.end(); ++it)
1608 _coeff.push_back(DataType(*it));
1609 }
1610
1611 ValueType value(const PointType& point) const
1612 {
1613 // evaluate polynomial via horner scheme
1614 DataType x = point[0];
1615 DataType y = DataType(0);
1616 for(std::size_t k(_coeff.size()); k > std::size_t(0); )
1617 y = x * y + _coeff[--k];
1618
1619 return y;
1620 }
1621
1622 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
1623 {
1624 std::size_t k = _coeff.size();
1625 if(k <= std::size_t(0))
1626 return GradientType::null();
1627
1628 // evaluate polynomial via horner scheme
1629 DataType x = point[0];
1630 DataType y = DataType(0);
1631 for( ; (--k) > std::size_t(0); )
1632 y = x * y + (_coeff[k] * DataType(k));
1633
1634 return GradientType(y);
1635 }
1636
1637 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point) const
1638 {
1639 std::size_t k = _coeff.size();
1640 if(k <= std::size_t(1))
1641 return HessianType::null();
1642
1643 // evaluate polynomial via horner scheme
1644 DataType x = point[0];
1645 DataType y = DataType(0);
1646 for( ; (--k) > std::size_t(1); )
1647 y = x * y + (_coeff[k] * DataType(k*(k-1)));
1648
1649 return HessianType(y);
1650 }
1651 }; // class PolynomialFunction1D::Evaluator
1652
1653 private:
1655 std::vector<DataType_> _coeff;
1656
1657 public:
1659 PolynomialFunction1D() :
1660 _coeff()
1661 {
1662 }
1663
1670 explicit PolynomialFunction1D(std::initializer_list<DataType_> coeff) :
1671 _coeff(coeff)
1672 {
1673 }
1674
1687 Index set_coeff(Index degree, DataType_ coeff)
1688 {
1689 // check degree
1690 if(Index(_coeff.size()) <= degree)
1691 _coeff.resize(std::size_t(degree+1), DataType_(0));
1692
1693 // set coefficient
1694 _coeff.at(std::size_t(degree)) = coeff;
1695
1696 // return degree+1
1697 return Index(_coeff.size());
1698 }
1699 }; // class PolynomialFunction1D

2054 public:
2061 ParProfileBase() :
2062 _x0(0.0), _y0(0.0), _x1(0.0), _y1(1.0), _vmax(1.0)

2065
2078 explicit ParProfileBase(DataType_ x0, DataType_ y0, DataType_ x1, DataType_ y1, DataType_ vmax = DataType_(1.0)) :
2079 _x0(x0), _y0(y0), _x1(x1), _y1(y1), _vmax(vmax)

2082
2100 bool parse(const String& sbc)
2101 {
2102 auto li = sbc.find_first_of('(');
2103 auto ri = sbc.find_last_of(')');
2104 if((li == sbc.npos) || (ri == sbc.npos))
2105 return false;
2106
2107 std::deque<String> sv = sbc.substr(li+1, ri-li-1).split_by_string(",");
2108 if((sv.size() < std::size_t(2)) || (sv.size() > std::size_t(3)))
2109 return false;
2110
2111 std::deque<String> sv0 = sv[0].trim().split_by_whitespaces();
2112 std::deque<String> sv1 = sv[1].trim().split_by_whitespaces();
2113 if(sv0.size() != std::size_t(2)) return false;
2114 if(sv1.size() != std::size_t(2)) return false;
2115
2116 if(!sv0[0].parse(_x0)) return false;
2117 if(!sv0[1].parse(_y0)) return false;
2118 if(!sv1[0].parse(_x1)) return false;
2119 if(!sv1[1].parse(_y1)) return false;
2120
2121 if((sv.size() == std::size_t(3)) && !sv.back().parse(_vmax))
2122 return false;
2123
2124 return true;
2125 }

2168 _ve[0] = DataType(function._x1 - function._x0);
2169 _ve[1] = DataType(function._y1 - function._y0);

2177 const DataType x = Math::clamp(Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den, DataType(0), DataType(1));
2178 // compute function value
2179 return _vmax * DataType(4) * x * (DataType(1) - x);
2180 }
2181
2182 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point)
2183 {
2184 // project point onto line segment
2185 const DataType x = Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den;
2186

2188 if((x < DataType(0)) || (x > DataType(1)))
2189 return GradientType::null();

2191 return (_vmax * _den * DataType(4) * (DataType(1) - DataType(2)*x)) * _ve;
2192 }
2193
2194 HessianType hessian(const PointType& point)
2195 {
2196 // project point onto line segment
2197 const DataType x = Tiny::dot(point - _vo, _ve) * _den;
2198
2199 // Note: the hessian has a singularity at x=0 and x=1
2200 if((x < DataType(0)) || (x > DataType(1)))
2201 return HessianType::null();
2202
2203 HessianType hess;
2204 const DataType v = -DataType(8) * _vmax * _den * _den;
2205 hess[0][0] = v * _ve[0] * _ve[0];
2206 hess[0][1] = hess[1][0] = v * _ve[0] * _ve[1];
2207 hess[1][1] = v * _ve[1] * _ve[1];

3210 const DataType re = pi / point.norm_euclid();
3211 return Math::sin(re*point[0]) * Math::sin(re*point[1]) * Math::sin(re*point[2]);
3212 }
3213
3214 GradientType gradient(const PointType& point) const
3215 {
3216 const DataType x = point[0];
3217 const DataType y = point[1];
3218 const DataType z = point[2];
3219 const DataType re = DataType(1) / point.norm_euclid();
3220 const DataType cx = Math::cos(pi * re * x);
3221 const DataType cy = Math::cos(pi * re * y);
3222 const DataType cz = Math::cos(pi * re * z);
3223 const DataType sx = Math::sin(pi * re * x);
3224 const DataType sy = Math::sin(pi * re * y);
3225 const DataType sz = Math::sin(pi * re * z);
3226 GradientType grad;
3227 grad[0] = +pi * Math::cub(re) * (cx*sz*sy*y*y + cx*sz*sy*z*z - sx*x*y*cy*sz - sx*sy*x*z*cz);
3228 grad[1] = -pi * Math::cub(re) * (x*y*cx*sy*sz - sz*sx*cy*x*x - sz*sx*cy*z*z + sx*sy*z*y*cz);
3229 grad[2] = -pi * Math::cub(re) * (x*z*cx*sy*sz + sx*z*y*cy*sz - sx*cz*sy*x*x - sx*cz*sy*y*y);
3230 return grad;

4248 _theta(function.theta),
4249 _sigma(function.sigma)
4250 {
4251 }
4252
4253 ValueType value(const PointType& point)
4254 {
4255 ValueType val = ValueType::null();
4256 const DataType d = point.norm_euclid();
4257 if(d < DataType(1E-3))
4258 return val;
4259
4260 const DataType x(point[0]), y(point[1]);
4261 const DataType q = DataType(1) / d;
4262 const DataType s2pdq = Math::sin(_pi2 * d) * q;
4263 const DataType c2pdq = Math::cos(_pi2 * d) * q;
4264
4265 val[0] = -_nu*q*y*( _pi2*c2pdq - (_pi2*_pi2*d + q)*s2pdq) - _beta*x*s2pdq*s2pdq + _theta*y*s2pdq - _sigma*x*c2pdq;
4266 val[1] = -_nu*q*x*(-_pi2*c2pdq + (_pi2*_pi2*d + q)*s2pdq) - _beta*y*s2pdq*s2pdq - _theta*x*s2pdq - _sigma*y*c2pdq;
4267 return val;
4268 }
